{"id": "EUVD-2025-201644", "enisaUuid": "5565526a-a4dd-3ef0-a07a-dc56011fe5dd", "description": "In the Linux kernel, the following vulnerability has been resolved:\n\nBluetooth: hci_event: validate skb length for unknown CC opcode\n\nIn hci_cmd_complete_evt(), if the command complete event has an unknown\nopcode, we assume the first byte of the remaining skb->data contains the\nreturn status. However, parameter data has previously been pulled in\nhci_event_func(), which may leave the skb empty. If so, using skb->data[0]\nfor the return status uses un-init memory.\n\nThe fix is to check skb->len before using skb->data.", "datePublished": "2025-12-08T03:31:01", "dateUpdated": "2025-12-08T03:31:01", "baseScore": 0.0, "references": ["https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/fea895de78d3bb2f0c09db9f10b18f8121b15759", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/779f83a91d4f1bf5ddfeaf528420cbb6dbf03fa8", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/cf2c2acec1cf456c3d11c11a7589e886a0f963a9", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/1a0ddaaf97405dbd11d4cb5a961a3f82400e8a50", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/5c5f1f64681cc889d9b13e4a61285e9e029d6ab5", "https://nvd.nist.gov/vuln/detail/CVE-2025-40301"], "aliases": ["CVE-2025-40301"], "assigner": "Linux", "epss": 0.02, "enisaIdProduct": [{"id": "05c414a6-6217-3821-941d-ca58aaeea1a3", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 6.17.8"}, {"id": "0afbbf19-0763-35ad-80fd-243038cb3cda", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "afcb3369f46ed5dc883a7b92f2dd1e264d79d388 <1a0ddaaf97405dbd11d4cb5a961a3f82400e8a50"}, {"id": "120c7964-c600-3816-88f1-bfa1c8b18b7c", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 6.6.117"}, {"id": "161a4d71-4cae-35df-ba49-5002b1a29ee5", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "afcb3369f46ed5dc883a7b92f2dd1e264d79d388 <5c5f1f64681cc889d9b13e4a61285e9e029d6ab5"}, {"id": "18de1335-5a60-3cba-82e6-d132c52d674e", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "afcb3369f46ed5dc883a7b92f2dd1e264d79d388 <779f83a91d